Hello!

I have spent the last 3 years working in EdTech. If you have a need for senior software developer, I would love to connect! Thank you!

Hi Brian,
Thanks for reaching out! I'd be happy to chat and learn more about what you have been working on, and your plans going forward. Are you free next Friday afternoon?

Yes! My schedule is pretty tight, could we have a phone call next Friday on your way out of the office at 5? My number is 4804660856. Thank you for the quick response! Mainly I've been working on a project called studysauce.com and Study Sauce in the iOS App Store. Invite code "demo" if you feel like checking it out ahead of time. It is like flash cards for students, and it reminds you to study based on what you get wrong or right.
Sure I will call you next week.
Thanks again, looking forward to it.
Is now a good time to talk?

I can email you a summary but LinkedIn doesn't display your email. One quick easy change to the Youtube player iframe and using the parameters modestbranding (hide youtube symbol), rel (hide suggested videos at the end) or listType (show a playlist)

I suppose if I were limited by equipment my first stop would be every educational incubator I could get my hands on building my network talking to foundations and board members to find more computer and pay people to set them up. My last step would probably be city council funding. Where are you on that front? Any relevance at all? ;)
Things are good - busy, hustling to get more customers signed up. I don't check linked in very often, so here's my email for future communication: kelly@prenda.co
